canonical:
  title: 慈州副使崔叔必讓起復不允批答
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 云云三年之喪天下之通制也然中古所以從權卽吉者本爲金革之事而朕已付爾以北方分憂之寄夫北方者接於強虜之邦常時尙爲用兵之地今則胡騎橫行倐來忽往故邊城守令無有投戈解甲而方晝夜戒嚴之時也汝於斯時將以親喪爲解而其不務忘家殉國之計耶云云
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 慈州副使崔叔必讓起復不允批答
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 云云。三年之喪。天下之通制也。然中古所以從權卽吉者。本爲金革之事。而朕已付爾以北方分憂之寄。夫北方者。接於強虜之邦。常時尙爲用兵之地。今則胡騎橫行。倐來忽往。故邊城守令。無有投戈解甲。而方晝夜戒嚴之時也。汝於斯時。將以親喪爲解。而其不務忘家殉國之計耶云云。
korean:
  title: 자주부사 최숙필 양 기복 불윤 비답
  author: 이규보
  language: kor
  text: 운운.3년의 상(喪)은 천하의 공통된 제도이다. 그러나 중고(中古) 이래로 권도(權道)를 좇아 상을 마치기 전에도 길복(吉服)을 입을 수 있게 한 것은 본시 전쟁의 일 때문이었다.짐이 이미 북방을 지키는 책임을 그대에게 맡겼다. 대개 북방은 강한 오랑캐의 나라와 접한 곳으로, 평상시에도 늘 군사를 쓰는 곳이다. 더구나 지금은 오랑캐 군사가 횡행하여 수시로 출몰하는 탓에 변성(邊城)의 수령들이 창을 놓고 갑옷을 벗을 겨를이 없이 바야흐로 밤낮으로 계엄하고 있는 때이다. 이러한 때에 그대는 어찌 친상(親喪)으로 인하여 집안일을 잊고 나라에 충성하는 일을 힘쓰지 않을 수 있겠는가. 운운.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0330_010_0070&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Royal Decree Denying the Request of Choe Suk-pil, Vice Administrator of Jazhou, to Resume Mourning
  author: Lee Gyeong-bo
  language: eng
  text: 'Your Majesty''s words continue thus: The three-year mourning period is the universal rite observed under Heaven. Yet since the middle ages, our predecessors have permitted the wearing of auspicious garments before mourning''s end, following the expedient way—all because of the exigencies of war. I have already entrusted you with the grave responsibility of guarding the northern frontier. Know that the north borders the lands of fierce barbarians; even in peaceful times it remains a place where arms must ever be ready. But now the Jurchen cavalry sweep across our borders, appearing and vanishing like phantoms. Your commanders and garrison leaders have no moment to lay down spear or unbuckle armor—day and night they stand vigilant. How can you, in such an hour, seek to set aside your duties through filial mourning? How can you forget the imperative to forsake family concerns and serve your nation? Your Majesty''s words continue thus.'
  footnotes:
    - This is a royal decree (批答) from the Korean Goryeo court, likely addressed to an official seeking early release from mourning obligations due to military necessity on the northern border.
    - The 'three-year mourning period' refers to the Confucian practice of mourning a parent for three years, which was a fundamental observance in medieval East Asia.
    - The reference to 'Jurchen cavalry' (胡騎) reflects the historical context of Goryeo's conflicts with northern invaders, particularly the Jurchen tribes.
